        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3250741532" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2921136834418694109">I&apos;ve had this on my radar for a while thanks to some of my nature writing loving friends, but this felt like the perfect time to read it. While the author is bedbound with a mysterious illness, she shares her small life with a wild snail. Through the course of the year she observes it closely, and later on incorporates research from translated poetry, early and contemporary science.<br/><br/>It&apos;s very much about dealing with circumstances that make life small, the beauty of small things, and so much more </span>
  <span id="freeText2921136834418694109" style="display:none">I've had this on my radar for a while thanks to some of my nature writing loving friends, but this felt like the perfect time to read it. While the author is bedbound with a mysterious illness, she shares her small life with a wild snail. Through the course of the year she observes it closely, and later on incorporates research from translated poetry, early and contemporary science.<br /><br />It's very much about dealing with circumstances that make life small, the beauty of small things, and so much more about snails than you ever knew you needed (but trust me, snails are amazing!)<br /><br /><i>I intend to come back to this space to add some bits I marked.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="2921136834418694109" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


